The paper discusses an automated tool for software bug fixing using Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) based Natural Language Processing. This falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. Additionally, the use of RNNs for NLP suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the Linux kernel, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY) categories.
